                                ocaml-fd
                                ~~~~~~~~

INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS:
==========================

These instructions assume you have Oasis installed.


Building:
---------

To build ocaml-fd, simply type the following:

$ make configure
$ make


Installing:
-----------

To install ocaml-fd, simply type "make install" in this directory.


Documentation:
--------------

Documentation generated by ocamldoc can be created by typing "make doc"
in this directory. The HTML files will reside in the "doc" directory.


Tests:
------

When you build ocaml-fd, some test executables will be created in test/ml,
namely "mycat" and "openfile". When run as "./mycat some_file", it will fork
and call "openfile", which will open the given file and send its descriptor to
its parent, using the functions provided by the Fd module. More details can be
found in the comments in test/ml/mycat.ml.
